2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning methods for data-driven discovery of Koopman operators. 
3. cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper deals with nonlinear dynamical systems and their Koopman operators. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning methods for identification and learning of nonlinear systems. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper's approach of using observable functions for approximating Koopman operators has similarities with neural network architectures, which fall under the purview of neural and evolutionary computing.
